            "response": "{\"Q0\":\"-\"}"
        },
        "0": {
            "rt": 149457.6000000015,
            "time_elapsed": 5932320,
            "response": "{\"Q0\":\"For the galaxy choice I picked one and kept looking up/down depending on which galaxy I picked. The planets had the exact same pattern of tools so I just had to pay attention to their color so I didn't have to look at the 'obstacles' (dirt rock or wood). I looked up/down because then I could focus on the area where the arrow for my picked galaxy would appear making it easier to click it in time.\"}"
        },
        "7": {
            "rt": 55539.199999999255,
            "time_elapsed": 6134706,
            "response": "{\"Q0\":\"I was hoping they would give me more gems then they did but it didn't impact my motivation.\"}"
        },
        "9": {
            "rt": 60486.5,
            "time_elapsed": 6357116,
            "response": "{\"Q0\":\"I paid more attention to he galaxies as they didn't have a fixed pattern as the planets, so they required my attention each time I had to make a choice. The plantets I just memorised\"}"
        },
        "1": {
            "rt": 64681.099999997765,
            "time_elapsed": 5997004,
            "response": "{\"Q0\":\"Well from the very begining I ignored the color yellow as there were no gems to be found there. Later on I started to ignore red as well because the astronaut flew away.\"}"
        },
        "2": {
            "rt": 39379.699999999255,
            "time_elapsed": 6036386,
            "response": "{\"Q0\":\"I didn't really pay attention to that but maybe around 40% of the time?\"}"
        },
        "8": {
            "rt": 161918.40000000224,
            "time_elapsed": 6296627,
            "response": "{\"Q0\":\"Basically I tried to do a proportion calculation to determine which option was more profitable with it's chance of happening. (so 1$ with 50% is better than 7% with 10% but not better than 7$ with 30%)\"}"
